node.text:
Join us July 11th for the start of a new space age. 

Aboard #Unity22, our first fully crewed rocket powered test flight, will be our team of two pilots and four mission specialists, including @RichardBranson. They will put our Future Astronaut spaceflight experience to a final test, while giving the world a preview of the life-changing experience. 
 
Be a part of this historic moment by watching LIVE on www.virgingalactic.com and our social media channels. 

Click the link in our bio to save the date - the countdown begins.

In this IGTV LIVE our very own Sirisha Bandla hosts a Q & A with @KellieGerardi. Kellie’s a bioastronautics researcher, mother, science communicator, commercial spaceflight advocate and #VirginGalactic payload specialist. 

She is set to realise her lifelong dream of experiencing space when she flies on a dedicated research mission, during which she will conduct experiments and test new healthcare technologies on behalf of the International Institute of Astronautical Sciences (IIAS).

node.text:
During a spaceflight, VMS Eve acts as a mothership and carries VSS Unity to release altitude.

These were routine flights for our pilots to complete regular proficiency checks. During the first flight, our pilots used VMS Eve to simulate SpaceShipTwo Unity’s glide and approach-to-land phase.

Pilots for the first flight were CJ Sturckow and Dave Mackay while in the cockpit for the second were Kelly Latimer and Mike "Sooch" Masucci.

VMS Eve is named after @richardbranson’s own mother, Eve, who sadly passed away this month. Eve was always cheering us on and will be immortalized through our beautiful carrier aircraft. As Richard said: "There's no way you can have a mothership and not name it after your mother!"
